<HEADLINE> Democratic Party to Hold National Convention in L.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic Party of the
United States announced that it will hold its national convention
for the 2000 presidential election in Los Angeles on August 14-17.
</P>
<P>
"On August 17, 2000, a new Democratic candidate will answer his
party's call to lead America into the next frontier," party
Chairman Joe Andrew said here Friday in announcing the convention
dates.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic National Committee announced last month that Los
Angeles had been chosen as the convention city. It is the first
time that the convention will be held in this city in 40 years.
The last Democratic convention held there was in 1960, when John
F. Kennedy was nominated as president.
</P>
<P>
The Republican Party will hold its 2000 national convention in
Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
The candidates for the 2000 presidential election are expected
to be nominated from both parties at their national conventions.
</P>
</TEXT>
