<HEADLINE> Blast in London Injures Several People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people were injured, some
seriously, in an explosion in a shopping street in south London
Saturday afternoon, BBC reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said there had been no warning and that the blast
was not believed to be related to the guerrilla conflict in
Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, Home Secretary Jack Straw condemned whoever
was responsible for the explosion.
</P>
<P>
"This is an outrageous and mindless act," Straw said.
</P>
<P>
"Our sympathies go out to those injured and their families and
to the family of the injured police officer," he added.
</P>
<P>
Shops and flats near the Iceland supermarket were damaged and
glass was scattered over a wide area.
</P>
<P>
One witness said the explosion happened when a boy moved a bag
that had been left between market stalls. The boy was said to have
suffered only minor injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
