<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Discuss Rights Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced Saturday
that it will organize a nation-wide discussion of the concept
paper on the establishment of the human rights commission and the
office of the ombudsman.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Aziz Ahmed, chairman of legal affairs standing committee
of the House of People's Representatives, told local press here
that the concept paper will be tabled for public discussion in all
states from April 27 to May 3.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Aziz said people's representatives, scholars,
legislators, executives, elders and various sections of the
society are expected to take part in the national discussion.
</P>
<P>
He said the concept paper which is prepared in Ahmaric,
Tigrigna, Oromiffa and Somali languages incorporates the
experiences of various countries world-wide.
</P>
<P>
Based on local realities, the public opinion and international
experiences, the draft proclamation establishing the human rights
institutions will be formulated and the bill is expected to be
approved this year, the chairman said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the institutions which will be instrumental in
protecting and ensuring the human and democratic rights of all
citizens in Ethiopia would become operational in late 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
