<HEADLINE> Chen Wins Second Gold at Chinese National Swimming Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAQING, Northeast China, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Asian
Games triple gold medalist Chen Hua won her second gold here when
she grabbed an individual title at the Chinese National Swimming
Champions Meet entered the second day here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
She won the 800m freestyle event Saturday evening by clocking
eight minutes 41.46 seconds, much slower than her 10th-ranked 1998
time of 8:39.40.
</P>
<P>
Chen, a 17-year-old freestyle specialist from East China's
Zhejiang Province, was a member of her native team which won
Friday's women's 4x200 meters freestyle relay.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who won the 400m and 800m freestyle and 4x200m freestyle
relay events at the Bangkok Games last December, qualified for the
finals here with the fastest time from Friday's heats.
</P>
<P>
Shan Ying from the People's Liberation Army's Guangzhou units
won her specialist event of 50m freestyle in 26.14 seconds. She
was ranked fourth in the world last year with a personal best time
of 25.36 of the year.
</P>
<P>
Asian Games champion Zeng Qiliang from south China's Guangdong
Province also won a second gold when he triumphed in the men's 100
m breaststroke in 1:01.89.
</P>
<P>
That time was 13 hundredths of a seconds slower than his best
time last year, which was ranked third in the year-ending world
rankings.
</P>
<P>
Zeng was chased neck-to-neck almost all the way by Asian Games
200m breaststroke champion Zhu Yi. Zeng only managed to edged his
closest rival in the final splash, winning by a narrow margin of
11 hundredths of a second.
</P>
<P>
Zeng has won Friday's men's 4x100 meter medley relay along with
his Guangdong teammates.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Yingjuan from Guangdong took the women's 100m backstroke
title in 1:03.53, beating triple gold-medalist Wu Yanyan into
second place.
</P>
<P>
Both Zeng Yingjuan and her coach Zhao Ge were not happy with
the result. She failed to sleep well for the last two weeks, which
might be blamed for a less impressive performance at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The team of Shandong added two more gold medals Saturday to
their opening triumph on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Fu Yong won the men's 200m backstroke in 2:01.02 and Hao ping
took the women's 200m breaststroke with 2:32.98.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's Zheng Shibin and Guangzhou's Qin Caini split honors
in the two other individual events -- men's 400m freestyle and the
women's 200m freestyle, while the city of Xi'an won the day's only
relay event, the men's 4x200m freestyle relay.
</P>
<P>
The National Champions' Meet closes on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
