<HEADLINE> OAU Should End Eritrea-Ethiopia War: Eritrea Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African Unity
(OAU) must speed up the implementation of last year's peace plan
to end the border conflict between Ethiopia and Eritrea, Eritrean
special envoy Kashai Ambemicael said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"There is a need to end the conflict since it has claimed many
lives," Ambemicael, who is Eritrea's Minister of Foreign Affairs,
told reporters here, after delivering a special message to
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe from Eritrean President Isayas
Afewerki.
</P>
<P>
Ambemicael updated Mugabe, who is chairman of the OAU conflict
resolution committee, on the fighting between the two neighbors
and diplomatic efforts that have been going on to end the war.
</P>
<P>
The conflict, Ambemicael said, should be solved through legal
and peaceful means by the demarcation of a boundary.
</P>
<P>
Since last May, the two countries have been fighting over a
1,000-km- long border strip both sides claim.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe is part of a heads-of-state group tasked with seeking a
diplomatic solution to the war. The group includes presidents of
Burkina Faso, Djibouti and Rwanda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
