<HEADLINE> Project Launched to Protect Yellow River Source </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A green project aimed at improving
the ecological environment of the fountainhead of the Yellow River,
was launched today in northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
The 20 million yuan project is the first in a series of actions
to protect the "mother rivers", which will be launched by the
Chinese government this year.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghai Plateau is the place where the Yellow, Yangtze and
Lancang rivers arise. Experts said that the ecological changes on
the plateau will have a major impact on the water volume and
quality in the middle and lower reaches of those rivers.
</P>
<P>
Affected by the bad weather conditions and human activities,
the ecological environment in the area is degrading.
</P>
<P>
The Longyang Gorge, where a major hydropower station on the
Yellow River is located, will be the first area targeted by the
project, which is jointly sponsored by the Communist Youth League
of China, the National Greening Committee, the Ministry of Water
Resources and other organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
