<HEADLINE> Kosgei Takes Rotterdam Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Japhet Kosgei won the Rotterdam
marathon after attacked three times before his final urge in 2
hours 7 minutes and 11 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan defeated defending titlist Fabian Roncero of Spain,
who finished second place in 2:07:24. Spaniard Julio Rey was third
in 2:07:38, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Tegla Loroupe made it a Kenyan double, winning the women's race
in the year's fastest time of 2:22.49.
</P>
