Ojima, South Korean Yi-Yong Kim, Morrocan Abdesalem Serrokh and
Kenyan and Simon Biwott.
</P>
<P>
Maase surprisingly stayed with the group till past the 37-
kilometer mark when first Serrokh and Ojima dropped back then Kim
was the next to go.
</P>
<P>
Roncero and Kosgei were alone when they passed 40 kilometers in
2:00:50, then Kosgei launched two unsuccessful breaks before
finally freeing himself inside the final kilometer.  
