<HEADLINE> Rockets Wins CBA First Game of Best-of-five Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Wang Zhizhi scored a game-high
26 points to pace the defending champions Bayi Rockets a 117-98
victory over the Liaoning Hunters in the first game of the best-of-
five finals Sunday at the Chinese Basketball Association league.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who aslo grabbed five rebounds and had three blocked-
shots, led six members of the Rockets in scoring double-figures,
whith Li Nan 18, Liu Qiang 17, Liu Yudong 16, Zhang Jinsong 13 and
Fan Bing 11, all of them were the members of the national team
winning the Asian Games men's basketball tournament in Bangkok
last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shouqiang was Liaoning's best with 24 points and six
rebounds, while American Hodges James hit 20 points eight rebounds.
</P>
<P>
The Bayi never trailed and led from the very beginning. They
easily built a lopsided lead 46-65 in the first half and 69-96 in
the third quarter before pulling away for the triumph.
</P>
<P>
The Rokets beat the Hunters in a straight three-game win for
their fourth consecutive league champions last season.  
</P>
