<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> General Ye Fei Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Ye Fei, one of China's
outstanding military commanders, died here at noon April 18, 1999
at the age of 85. He had been ill for some time.
</P>
<P>
Ye, an outstanding member of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
was a long-tested loyal communist fighter and a great proletarian
revolutionary. He served as the vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee of the sixth and seventh National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
He joined the Communist Youth League of China on May 1928 and
became a CPC member on March 1932. In the same year, he joined the
Red Army. Ye was conferred with the rank of general in 1955.
</P>
</TEXT>
