<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan on Political Education, Social Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, today stressed the education in theoretical studies,
political awareness and good conducts across the country.
</P>
<P>
The education should be carried out to improve the quality of
government officials at all levels, noted Li, who is also a member
of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Li made the comments during an inspection tour in north China's
Hebei province which took in a number of state-owned enterprises
and discussed with various leaders and company chiefs how to step
up reform and improve the economic results in state-run
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that social stability will be especially
important this year, when some major historical events will take
place.
</P>
<P>
"First of all, the relation between reform, development and
stability should be carefully dealt with," said Li.
</P>
<P>
He said that officials should be concerned with the lives of
ordinary people, listen to their complaints and try to settle
problems for them.
</P>
<P>
He added that various major cases should be settled in
accordance with law, and a handful of criminals who have brought
hazard to social stability should be severely punished. 
</P>
</TEXT>
