<HEADLINE> Chinese Army Enhances Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Theoretical education has been
enhanced in the Chinese army and the armed police force in line
with the requirements of the Central Military Commission of the
People's Republic of China and the General Political Department of
the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
Leading officers of the PLA's Headquarters of the General Staff,
General Political Department, General Logistics Department and
General Armament Department said that President Jiang Zemin's call
for educating Communist Party members and government officials
with the focus on theoretical study, political awareness and
healthy ethics is a strategic decision conducive to the prosperity
of the country, the construction of the Party and ensuring correct
guidance for troops.
</P>
<P>
They asked all the military area commands, the navy, air force,
second artillery force, and the armed police force to regard
education as an important measure to improve the Party's spirit
and work style.
</P>
<P>
They believe that the new situation of the opening up and
reform means that the army should be politically firm and should
give more emphasis to hi-technology. 
