<HEADLINE> Westwood Wins Macao Golf Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- World number seven Lee Westwood
of England won the 200,000 U.S. dollar Macao Open at the second
extra hole on Sunday, according to an Asian PGA Tour press release
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The Briton parred the par-five 18th to beat American Andrew
Pitts, who had forced the additional holes with a birdie at the
last in regulation play.
</P>
<P>
Westwood, who finished sixth at the U.S. Masters last week,
scored the final round one-under-par 70 for a nine-under total of
275. It was Westwood's 14th career victory, his sixth in Asia and
his sixth in a playoff.
</P>
<P>
Pitts matched Westwood's birdie from 18 foot at the first
playoff hole but three-putted the second time around from 40 foot
for a bogey and defeat.
</P>
<P>
"I do all right in playoffs," said Westwood. "I have been in
seven and won six but this was the hardest to win."
</P>
<P>
Japan's Reigning champion Satoshi Oide closed with a 70 to tie
for third place with South Africa's James Kingston (67).
</P>
<P>
Zhang Liangwei, China's number one, finished fifth for a five-
under-par total of 279 with four other players. 
</P>
</TEXT>
