<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Chen Yan Pulls out of Chinese National Swimming Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAQING, Northeast China, April 18 (Xinhua) -- World champion
Chen Yan has withdrawn from the on-going Chinese national swimming
champions meet, her coach Han Bingyan confirmed on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Chen has just resumed training for two weeks after a lay-off
for almost four months, due to medical treatment for her stomach
problems," Han said.
</P>
<P>
Chen, world record holder of women's 400 meters individual
medley, had entered for the 200m discipline scheduled for Monday,
which would have been her first race after the long rest.
</P>
<P>
"She is still quite weak although she is now four kilograms
heavier than before, with the weight put on during the treatment.
Her current weight of 63 kilograms is still not satisfactory for a
world-level swimmer standing 1.79 meters," Han said.
</P>
<P>
The national champions meet is the first qualifying tournament
for this September's National Cities Games in Xi'an. Now she has
to compete in the second such qualifier meet slated for June in
her native town of Dalian.
</P>
<P>
"The most important thing for her is to get recovered, so as to
start real preparations for next year's Olympic Games in Sydney,"
Han added. 
</P>
