<HEADLINE> Defense Ministry Employees Demonstrate Over Wages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Several hundred representatives
of the Israeli Defense Ministry employees demonstrated in front of
the Prime Minister's residence Sunday, urging the government to
strike a wage deal with them.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Moshe Arens met the demonstrators, saying he
supports their demand for wage increase.
</P>
<P>
But Arens called on them to cancel their demonstration and strike
which has lasted for weeks, and solve the problem through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry employees demand equal wage treatment with
other military services, threatening to continue strikes till their
demands are met.
</P>
<P>
The employees have refused to release military goods at Israeli
ports and airport, to arrange activities for ministry officers and to
handle the daily business at the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The work stopage has badly affected the operations of certain
defense agencies in the country, which has also caused some worries
among the senior military brass.
</P>
<P>
But so far, the Finance Ministry has rejected to increase their
wage scales and reach any agreement with them.
</P>
<P>
In March, some 400,000 Israeli public sector workers launched a
nationwide strike, forcing the government to increase their wages by
about 4.8 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
