<HEADLINE> World Cup Champion Sang Wins First Naitonal Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Double World Cup champion Sang Xue
won her first national title in the women's 10-meter platform
event at the National Champion's Diving Tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sang, 15, who made a golden double in the sychronized and
singles platform events at the World Cup tournament in New Zeland
last January, collected 609.99 points for the title.
</P>
<P>
Li Na, who paired Sang to win the World Cup synchronized,
finished second in 579.79 points, while Wang Rui was third in 558.
69.
</P>
<P>
Sang, who began diving at 10, advanced into the finals as
second placer of the qualifying round. She made a string of
spectacular dives in the five-round finals and scored 74.76, 78.12,
90.24, 89.10 and 85.50 pionts.
</P>
<P>
Sang won her first title in the sychronized 10m platform at the
Goodwill Games in New York last July. Taht was her first time to
take part in an international competition.
</P>
<P>
"She was the first Chinese diver who had captured a title in
world competitions before getting a naitonal one," her coach Wang
Min said.
</P>
<P>
"Her dives are very elegant, very beautiful," said Zhou Jihong,
the 1984 Olympic women's platform champion and now the manager of
the Chinese national diving team. "She has had the calibre to win
the Olympic gold medals." 
</P>
