<HEADLINE> Japanese Youth Delegation Ends China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Tokyo Junior
Chamber Incorporation ended a four-day visit to China and left for
home this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Beijing, Vice-Chairman Hu Qili of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) met with the Japanese guests.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, together with the All-China Youth Federation (
ACYF), also conducted activities to celebrate the 50th anniversary
of the two institutions. The delegation members also exchanged
views with relevant Chinese departments on such issues as economic
and trade cooperation and youth training.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo Junior Chamber Incorporation, an unofficial economic
group composed of managers from small and medium-sized enterprises,
established its Japan-China Friendship Association in 1975 and
received a group of Chinese graduates sent by the ACYF in 1980.
</P>
