<HEADLINE> More Kurdish Rebels Killed in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) rose to 39 in the two-day armed clashes
with Turkish security forces in eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Local Turkiye Daily reported Sunday that the clashes occurred
Friday morning when a group of PKK militants launched attacks on a
convoy of government troops, which were dispatched in Cicekli-Dinar
region in Tunceli province.
</P>
