Kurdish state in southeatern Turkey, which has claimed over 37,000
lives.
</P>
<P>
Its leader, Abdullah Ocalan, was captured by the Turkish government
and detained on Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near Turkey's western
province of Bursa, waiting for trial on charges of treason.
</P>
<P>
A series of bombing attacks have been launched by Kurdish rebels in
protest of the arrest of Ocalan by Turkish special agents in
mid-February in Kenya. 
