<HEADLINE> Unique Limestone Caves Found In North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A group of unusual limestone
caves were found recently in the western part of Mancheng County
in China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The caves are halfway up the face of the Taihang Mountains.
Geologists did a month study of them and say that there are many
unusual stalactites, stone pillars, and stalagmites that are
rarely seen in the northern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities say that they could be used as a scenic spot.
Geologists have also found fossils of tigers and bears that could
help with research on the area's geological and biological
development.  
</P>
