<HEADLINE> Cholera Strikes Tanzanian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Cholera has made an evil
comeback to Tanzanian capital Dar es Salaam, affecting more than
30 people in the city.
</P>
<P>
No deaths have been reported, but the City Medical Officer, Deo
Mtasiwa, have appealed people to observe hygiene to avoid
contracting the communicable disease.
</P>
<P>
Sunday Observer newspaper said the cholera has badly affected
seven areas of the city, and 35 people have been admitted to
hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Mtasiwa has appealed to the public to maintain basic sanitation
 standards, urging people to keep their food clean, boil drinking
water, and refrain from eating food sold by vendors.
</P>
<P>
He also called on people to built toilets and make use of them
instead of helping themselves in the bush.
</P>
<P>
Cholera is one of the leading killer diseases in Tanzania,
together with AIDS and malaria. Last month, two people died of
cholera in the city.  
</P>
