<HEADLINE> Lightening Razed Down Building Complex in Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NAIROBI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A storey building complex
housing two merchant companies and two consulting offices was
struck Saturday by lightening which gutted a high volume of
property including a BMW saloon car.
</P>
<P>
 The building, situated in the Adabraka suburb, was completely
razed down but with no human casualties.
</P>
<P>
 The BMW car which was packed behind the building was
completely burnt while collapsing walls crushed computers and
office accessories.
</P>
<P>
The companies housed in the building were National Trust
Holding Company, BKB Couriers Ghana Ltd, Task Consultancy, and
PAO Andahs and Associates.
</P>
<P>
 Tonny Lawoe, Greater Accra regional fire commander said a
combined team of fire fighters including those from the military
could not help much because information on the blaze reached them
late, Ghana News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Eye witnesses were said to have stood helpless as the blaze
gradually consumed the building.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's rains had been the most persistent in recent times
leaving in its wake flooded streets in most parts of the
capital.  
</P>
