<HEADLINE> Raptors Beat Knicks to End Losing Streak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Toronto Raptors snapped a
season-high six-game losing streak as rookie Vince Carter scored
21 points, including a pair of 3-pointers in the final minute, for
a 93-90 victory over the New York Knicks on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After Patrick Ewing put in two free throws to pull the Knicks
81-84, Carter drilled a 3-pointer with 71 seconds to go, keeping
the Raptors away from squandering its 21-point second-quarter lead.
</P>
<P>
Allan Houston responded with a 3-pointer to halve the deficit,
but Carter made another 3-pointer with 44 seconds to play.
</P>
<P>
Toronto (19-20), which never make the playoffs, remained tied
with Charlotte and moved within one game of New York (21-20),
which is ninth in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
Latrell Sprewell scored 22 points off the bench and Houston
added 17 for the Knicks, who have lost three in a row, and would
miss the playoffs should being tied in the eighth place with the
Raptors as the latter held a 2-1 away advantage.
</P>
<P>
In Utah, John Stockton savored his 13,000th career assist and
Karl Malone scored 27 points as the Jazz routed the Los Angeles
Lakers 109-93 for their 10th straight victory.
</P>
<P>
As Dennis Rodman was waived Thursday, J.R. Reid and Travis
Knight split the power forward position and combined for one point
and six rebounds in 44 minutes.
</P>
<P>
With the longest winning streak in the NBA this season, the
Jazz, at 31-8, are 1 1/2 games ahead of Portland for the league's
best record and home-court advantage throughout the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers (25-16) have lost three straight and are fifth in
the West, two games behind Houston.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, Greg Anthony scored 17 of his season-high 23 points
in the fourth quarter, including all four of his 3-pointers, as
the Portland Trail Blazers pulled out a 101-92 victory over the
Dallas Mavericks for their seventh straight win over Dallas.
</P>
<P>
In Cleveland, David Wesley scored 24 points as the surging
Hornets extended their season-high winning streak to seven games
with a 90-82 victory over the Cavaliers in a key Eastern
Conference battle.
</P>
<P>
Elden Campbell and Eddie Jones, traded from the Lakers, helped
the Hornets close to within one game of .500 (19-20) and within 1
1/2 games of the Cavaliers for the Eastern Conference's final
playoff berth.
</P>
<P>
In Sacramento, Corliss Williamson scored a season-high 29
points and Chris Webber added 24 as the Kings recorded a 119-97
rout of the Denver Nuggets and climbed within 1 1/2 games of
Seattle for the final playoff spot in the Western Conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
