<HEADLINE> Frazier Wins Japan Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- American Ami Frazier scored an
identical 6-2 to topple defending champion Ai Sugiyama of Japan to
win her second Japan Open women's tennis championship here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Frazier, winner of the tournament in 1995,
broke error-prone Sugiyama at love in the opening set's fifth and
seventh games before closing out the set in 29 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sugiyama, the 23-year-old top seed who ranked 27th in the world,
put up little resistance in the second set, going down in the same
score as her American opponent scored points with tough returns
and serves.
</P>
<P>
It was Frazier's fifth appearance in the tournament final since
1994. Her fourth came in 1997, when she lost 6-4, 4-6, 4-6 to
Sugiyama who retained the title last year. 
</P>
