<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Pilgrims Return Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- All 1,101 pilgrims from the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have returned home safely as a
chartered plane carrying the last group of pilgrims landed at the
Urumqi Airport this morning.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang, the largest autonomous region in northwest China, is
the home of 8 million Muslim minority ethnic people.
</P>
<P>
Each year, thousands of Muslims from Xinjiang go to Mecca,
Islam's holiest city in Saudi Arabia, to perform the annual
religious pilgrimage, known as the hajj, which is required of
every able-bodied Muslim who can afford it at least once in their
life.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Airlines began offering chartered planes for the hajj
in 1995, and over the past five years the airline has transported
nearly 10,000 pilgrims.
</P>
<P>
In the middle of March, the airline dispatched four chartered
planes to carry the pilgrims to Mecca. 
</P>
