<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reinsurer Fights for Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The newly founded China
Reinsurance Company (China Re) is facing severe competition from
overseas counterparts, which took over 90 percent of China's non-
compulsory reinsurance business last year.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with China's Insurance law, all insurance
companies must reinsure their business at China Re, the only
reinsurance company in China, with 20 percent of their premium
income (compulsory reinsurance), today's Business Weekly reported.
</P>
<P>
As to non-compulsory reinsurance, or commercial reinsurance,
domestic companies are free to choose between China Re and
overseas reinsurance firms, the English newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
Many direct insurance firms have played tricks to avoid
compulsory reinsurance and handed out non-compulsory reinsurance
abroad, according to Dai Fengju, general manager of China Re.
</P>
<P>
The compulsory reinsurance rate was only 19 percent, while the
claim settlement rate was 3 to 5 percent higher than it should
have been.
</P>
<P>
The picture for non-compulsory reinsurance looked even worse.
In 1998 alone, 500 million U.S. dollars in reinsurance premiums
went to overseas companies, wasting much of the domestic
underwriting capacity.
</P>
<P>
Formed on the basis of the former People's Insurance (
Reinsurance) Company of China, which was set up in 1995, China Re
had a registered capital of 3 billion yuan (362 million U.S.
dollars) and a long-term liability reserve fund of 6 billion yuan
(723 million dollars) at its founding on March 19 this year.
</P>
<P>
China Re has mapped out a plan to become one of the top 10
reinsurance companies in the world in terms of scale, quality,
management, and profit, Dai said.
</P>
<P>
The watchdog of China's insurance industry, the China Insurance
Regulatory Commission, will step up its efforts this year to lay
down a reinsurance management regulation, said Wu Dingfu, vice-
chairman of the commission, at the first national reinsurance
conference held since the founding of China Re.
</P>
<P>
The regulation will set up detailed principles on the position
of China Re, the administration of compulsory reinsurance, the
operation of the domestic reinsurance market, and the punishments
for violating companies, Wu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
