<HEADLINE> 2 S.Lanka Policemen Injured, 3 Missing in Rebel Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Two Sri Lankan policemen were
seriously injured and three others were missing in a mortar attack
by Tamil rebels in Vavuniya in the Northern Province of the
country Saturday, reports reaching here said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) fired mortars at policemen manning a bunker in a newly
cleared area in the province.
</P>
<P>
An army spokesman said the three missing policemen including a
sub-inspector may have been killed in the mortar attack and their
bodies may have been removed from the spot by the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a war against the government
since 1983 for a separate state in the country.
</P>
<P>
Further investigations are under way, the reports said.
</P>
</TEXT>
