<DOCNO> XIE19990418.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Hotels Looking Forward to Birthday Boom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Tourists usually have no problems
finding hotel rooms in Beijing. The occupancy rate of the city's
star-rated hotels averages about 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, they will be unable to reserve a well-positioned room
at the Beijing Hotel and Grand Hotel Beijing during the days close
to October 1, the 50 anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China, today's Business Weekly reported today.
</P>
<P>
More than 98 percent of the two hotels' rooms are booked, said
hotel sources, even though the room rates had been nearly doubled
for those days.
</P>
<P>
"The central government's decision to hold a grand ceremony to
celebrate the 50th National Day brings enormous business
opportunities for star-rated hotels along Chang'an Avenue,
especially the Beijing Hotel and the Grand Hotel Beijing," the
newspaper quoted Yu Debin of the Beijing Tourism Administration (
BTA).
</P>
<P>
Tourists and State guests want to get a close view of the
century's last grand ceremony held in Beijing, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Meng Xuenong, deputy director of the Beijing
Preparatory Committee for the 50th Anniversary, a review of troops
and a grand parade will be held in Beijing on October 1.
</P>
<P>
China last held a military parade in 1984 to mark the 35th
anniversary of the founding of New China. Following the review on
October 1, there will be a grand parade involving tens of
thousands of people.
</P>
<P>
Some 500,000 people will participate in the celebrations, troop
review, and grand parade in the heart of Beijing, which are
scheduled to last about two hours on National Day.
</P>
<P>
On the evening of October 1, there will be a gala event
involving 100,000 people at Tian'anmen Square. At the same time,
there will be various galas hosted by workers, farmers,
intellectuals, soldiers, cadres, students, and people of different
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Tian'anmen Square will be lit by fireworks, as Party and State
leaders gather on the Tian'anmen Rostrum to watch performances
together with representatives from many walks of life.
</P>
<P>
To take advantage of the event, many star-rated hotels,
especially those situated along Chang'an Avenue, began seeking
tourists through the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Local media have declared that Beijing's hotel rooms will be in
short supply during those days.
</P>
<P>
The occupancy rate of Beijing star-rated hotel dropped to less
than 50 percent in 1998 from 59 percent in 1997 and 63 percent in
1996 as an adverse impact of the Asian financial crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
