<HEADLINE> Chinese Trade, Economic Delegation Visits Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese government trade and
economic delegation arrived here Sunday for a week-long official
visit aimed at enhancing China's trade and economic ties with
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Sun Guangxiang, deputy minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, was greeted at the
Pochentong Airport by Secretary of state for the Ministry of
Finance Kong Vibol.
</P>
<P>
Sun told reporters his visit is to implement the cooperation
agreement reached by the two countries during Prime Minister Hun
Sen's visit to China in February.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed his delegation's visit will help deepen
understanding and friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It is the first Chinese government trade and economic
delegation to visit Cambodia since the new coalition government
was formed in November 1998.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the delegation will meet Prime Minister Hun
Sen, Senate President Chea Sim, National Assembly President Prince
Norodom Ranariddh and other senior government officials. It will
hold trade talks with some ministries concerned.
</P>
<P>
The 22-member Chinese delegation including 14 representatives
of Chinese enterprises will also conduct an on-the-spot
investigation of the projects to be implemented by Cambodia with
loans provided by the Chinese government. 
</P>
