<HEADLINE> China Expresses Indignation at Anti-China Speech by Japanese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China expressed its indignation
today at an anti-China speech made by newly elected Governor of
Metropolitan Tokyo Ishihara Shintaro.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today
that "we are indignant at the fact that Ishihara wantonly made a
speech which hurts the feelings of the Chinese people and impairs
the Sino-Japanese ties."
</P>
<P>
He said this when asked to comment on anti-China remarks
Ishihara made on a public occasion recently.
</P>
<P>
Ishihara's act of openly spreading the views of beautifying the
aggression history of Japan's militarism and the absolutely absurd
anti-China views goes against the historical trend while the
governments and peoples of China and Japan are pushing forward the
development of the bilateral relations in the spirit of taking
history as a mirror and gearing towards the future, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
He added that to pursue Sino-Japanese friendship is not only in
the fundamental interests of the peoples of the two countries, but
also reflects their common aspirations.
</P>
<P>
"Ishihara's clumsy performance is unpopular, and will certainly
be opposed by the peoples of the both countries," he noted. "We
warn him not to continue on his erroneous track," Sun added.
