<HEADLINE> Leather Firms Urged to Develop Famous Brands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's leather firms are called
on to make efforts to foster famous brands nationwide in the face
of current difficulties in the sector, the Business Weekly said
today.
</P>
<P>
China is short of real famous brands for its leather garments,
although it dominates the world leather production after years of
development, the Beijing-based English language newspaper quoted
an official with the China Leather Industry Association (CLIA) as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"There are dozens of locally famous brands in provinces or
major cities, but we cannot say we have brands recognized by
people nationwide," said Li Yuzhong, deputy secretary-general of
the association.
</P>
<P>
China's leather products exports totaled 10 billion U.S.
dollars last year and exports were expected to increase 7 percent
annually, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Small scale production and lack of famous brands in the
international market are the major problems the leather firms are
facing, he added.
</P>
<P>
Small and medium-sized firms account for 97 percent of the
industry, and most of them are located in the coastal provinces in
east and south China.
</P>
<P>
Design and manufacturing techniques also need to be upgraded in
accordance with international trends as leather garments are no
longer a luxury for many Chinese people with the improvement of
living standards, according to Ying Zecong, manager of the Tianjin
Yingdak (Taiwan) Leather and Fashion Co Ltd.  
</P>
</TEXT>
