<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Growth In China's Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region had 20 more overseas-funded enterprises in the first
quarter of the year, worth nearly 71 million US dollars of
overseas investment, a jump of 88 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Four of the new enterprises have more than 10 million US
dollars of overseas investment each and 8 are wholly-owned by
overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Three-fourth of the overseas investment of the period, or 53
million US dollars, was from Asia.
</P>
<P>
The region had 29 overseas labor service projects, worth 12.26
million US dollars of investment. 
