<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- 80.5 percent of Peruvians say that
unemployment is a main problem facing the country, while 25.5
percent express that they are affected seriously by poverty and
hunger, a poll revealed on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the Marketing Studies IMA firm among 400
people, reflects the Peruvians' dissatisfaction with the efforts
to solve the unemployment and poverty problems.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that some four million people are
living in poverty in Peru, and even more in extreme poverty.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that some three million people are unemployed
or underemployed. Many of them said they are older than 35.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, the Peru's government has made
efforts to reactivate the economy in order to create more jobs.
