<HEADLINE> Easy Victory for Man United </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- One goal each from Ole Gunnar
Solskjaer, Teddy Sheringham and Paul Scholes gave Manchester
United an easy 3-0 home victory over Sheffield Wednesday at the
English Premier League on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Manchester United extended its leading place to
four points against second-placed Arsenal.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal and third-placed Chelsea play later over the weekend
but Leeds United missed a chance to close ground when they could
only draw 1-1 at 10-man Charlton Athletic.
</P>
<P>
Everton were the only one of the bottom seven to win 3-1 at
Newcastle - and they climb to 15th place, above Coventry who were
dragged back into the relegation battle with a 2-1 home defeat by
Middlesbrough
</P>
<P>
Nottingham Forest are all but doomed after losing 1-0 at home
to Tottenham Hotspur but second-last Southampton are still hoping
for safety after fighting back from 3-1 down to draw 3-3 at home
to third-from bottom Blackburn Rovers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
