<HEADLINE> Tergat Wins Half Marathon in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Paul Tergat of Kenya run to an easy
victory in the Stramilano Half Marathon but failed to surpass the
record time he set up one year ago in Milan, Italy on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan, fresh off his fifth straight cross country world
title, crossed the finish line in 59 minutes and 22 seconds, five
seconds away from the world best for the distance he ran here in
1998.
</P>
<P>
Tergat claimed a record fifth consecutive cross country crown
in Belfast, Northern Ireland, last month.
</P>
<P>
Paul Koech, also Kenyan, was second Saturday in 1:00:34, who
captured the half marathon world championship by clocking 1:00:01
at Zurich, Switzerland, in September.
</P>
<P>
Following are the top ten finishers:
</P>
<P>
1. Paul Tergat, Kenya, 59 minutes 22 seconds
</P>
<P>
2. Paul Koech, Kenya, 1:00:34
</P>
<P>
3. John Korir, Kenya, 1:01:59
</P>
<P>
4. Douglas Rono, Kenya, 1:02:04
</P>
<P>
5. Roberto Barbi, Italy, 1:02:09
</P>
<P>
6. Armando Quintanilla, Mexico, 1:02:25
</P>
<P>
7. Giovanni Battocletti, Italy, 1:02:32
</P>
<P>
8. Edoardo Enriques, Portugal, 1:03:12
</P>
<P>
9. Daniel Kirwa Too, Kenya, 1:03:22
</P>
<P>
10. Rosario Daidone, Italy, 1:04:22. 
</P>
