<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Takes First Two Singles over Belarus in Fed Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic took a
comfortable 2-0 lead by winning the first two singles matches over
Belarus in the Federation Cup World Group two playoffs in Minsk,
Belarus on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the first-day singles, Denisa Chadkova defeated top-ranked
Belarusian Natasha Zvereva 6-3, 7-6 (7-3), while Kvetoslava
Hrdlickova overpowered Olga Barabanschikova 6-1, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Zvereva who ranked 17, was unable to overcome the 118th-ranked
Chladkova despite her early lead of 2-0 after she lost four
consecutive games in the first set.
</P>
<P>
From 3-5, Zvereva fired two aces to overtake the lead 6-5 in
the second set, but lost the tiebreaker as Chadkova won the first
four points for her first win in two tries for the Czech Republic
in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Hrdlickova needed only 58 minutes to defeat
Barabanschikova in straight sets as the latter committed eight
double faults for 0-5 in the first set.
</P>
<P>
Once lead 2-0 in the second set, the Belarusian lost four
consecutive games, two of them to love, and was never back in the
match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
