<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Increases In Central Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's Henan Province reported
a 300 percent rise in the overseas investment contracts on a year-
on-year basis to 184.7 million US dollars worth during the first
quarter.
</P>
<P>
The province added 45 overseas-funded enterprises during the
three-month period, including 29 joint ventures and 9 solely-
foreign-owned companies.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-two of the enterprises are involved in manufacturing.
Eighteen of them are located in the provincial capital Zhengzhou.
</P>
<P>
The province now has more than 6,000 overseas-funded
enterprises and has used more than 3.3 billion US dollars worth of
overseas investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
